    "causal_summary": "The 029 model benchmark found memory search confidently cited an off-corpus term, kubernetes scored good on a semantically unrelated doc across all four models, and the 030 improvement research diagnosed a score-calibration miss. The verdict and citation path scores good and cite_results from the absolute cosine plus a top-margin alone, with no query-term or lexical-grounding signal, so a fluent off-corpus term sails through on one spurious high-cosine hit. A lone above-floor hit also reaches good through qualityRatio with a zero margin, so the margin signal rewards the spurious hit. This phase gates good and cite_results on a lexical-grounding floor and requires single-hit corroboration in assessRequestQuality, both behind a default-OFF flag so the shipped verdict prose existing spec docs carry stays accurate until graduation.",
